{"questionId":"28153","questionHtml":"<p>The activation energy of a reaction can be obtained from the rate constant, <em>k</em>, and the&nbsp;absolute temperature, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T</mtext></math>. Which graph of these quantities produces a straight line?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; <em>k</em> against <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T</mtext></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <em>k</em> against&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mtext>T</mtext></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;ln <em>k</em> against&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T</mtext></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; ln <em>k</em> against <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mtext>T</mtext></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"28153","referenceCode":"22N.1.hl.TZ0.21","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The activation energy of a reaction can be obtained from the rate constant, k, and the absolute temperature, T. Which graph of these quantities produces a straight line? A. k again","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"21","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics","16.1 Rate expression and reaction mechanism","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}